  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Two more I. w. w. leaders have\n\n\nbeen ground through the mill in\nJustice Suckers court. Yesterday\nafternoon James p. Thompson, an\norganizer, was sentenced to six\n\n\nmonths in Jail, and this morning A.\ne. Cousins, former associate editor\nof the local Industrial paper, was\n\n\nfound guilty and sentenced to four\nmonths in Jail.\n\n\nThings are going along with\ngreater dispatch in these last trials.\nThis morning 1t required only thirty\nminutes to try and sentence Cous-\nms. while it is expected that even\nquicker time will be made in some\nof the remaining cases.\n\n\nThe l. w. w. leaders yet to be\ntried for conspiracy are s. L. Bailey,\n\n\nElizabeth G. Flynn Jones, Louis\nGatewood, f. NJ. Conner, William\nDouglas and G. II. Speed. Mrs.\n\n\nJones, or Gurley Flynn, as she is\nbetter known, is out on $4,000 bond,\nwhile the others remain in Jail.\nIn each case notice of appeal\n\n\nhas been filed with bonds fixed at\n\n\n81 900."
    }
